.TH "do_splice_direct" 9 "do_splice_direct" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_splice_direct \- splices data directly between two files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" do_splice_direct
.BI "(struct file *in "  ","
.BI "loff_t *ppos "  ","
.BI "struct file *out "  ","
.BI "loff_t *opos "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "in" 12
file to splice from
.IP "ppos" 12
input file offset
.IP "out" 12
file to splice to
.IP "opos" 12
output file offset
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to splice
.IP "flags" 12
splice modifier flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For use by \fBdo_sendfile\fP. splice can easily emulate sendfile, but
doing it in the application would incur an extra system call
(splice in + splice out, as compared to just \fBsendfile\fP). So this helper
can splice directly through a process-private pipe.
